   "description": "Karl Iwan Sigfrid Broberg was a Swedish artist born on July 27, 1887, in Söndrum, Halland. He was married once to Anna Andersson and had two children, Gösta (born in 1914) and Rune (born in 1922). He was a member of several art associations and his artwork is represented in various collections. Broberg painted landscapes, still life, marine, and street scenes, and held exhibitions in several cities. He also pursued technical and correspondence education in Sweden and studied in several countries including North America, Norway, Denmark, and England."
